Package Classes.Listing.Item

Class Item

java.lang.Object
Classes.Listing.Item.Item
public class Item
extends java.lang.Object
Represents an "Item" or "Listing" as it is represented in the app.

    • createdByUserId

      public long createdByUserId
      The ID of the user who created the item originally.

      NOTE: this is not the userLoginId (which is a GUID or string). It is the userId, which is a long.

      Set By:
      The frontend Android app when saving a new item, using userId of the user who is logged in
      Set When:
      Creating a new item on the frontend Android application.
      Can Be Modified By:
      No one.
      Can Be Modified When:
      Never. This should not be modified once set.

    • updatedByUserId

      Set By:
      The frontend Android app when saving a new item, using userId of the user who is logged in
      Set When:
      Creating a new item on the frontend Android application.
      Can Be Modified By:
      The Android application.
      Can Be Modified When:
      Saving an existing item in the frontend Android application.

    • id

      public java.lang.Long id
      The ID of the item. This is the primary key identifying the item in the database.

      NOTE: This will be NULL when creating a new item in the app. It is not set until the item is saved.

      Set By:
      The database (should be set to autoincrement)
      Set When:
      A new item is saved to the database
      Can Be Modified By:
      No one.
      Can Be Modified When:
      Never.
